Psychology of the Posts: Why do we spend more money?
The participants in the subcontractors are willing to spend more money and overestimate the product.
The neurologists and economists of New York University discovered the neurological bases - economics of this known and apparently irrational behavior.
According to the study in Science magazine, people don't want to lose skills such as the eBay substations, so they prefer to pay even an excessive price.
Scientists tried to establish the neurological scheme of this "game" through experimental substances.
One of the volunteer groups played lottery, the other participated in a summit and while both were examined through the functional magnetic resonance system (fMRI) the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could earn money, but during the substances, where it is essential to put more than the other, when losing the game was intensified the operation of the complex called strata located below the brain cortex.
This brain area, in addition to many other functions, plays a role in the "car award" mechanism of the nervous system.
Thus, according to scientists, the increase in seizures is explained as a prevention to prevent an intense reaction to the strata.
In order to base their theory, the economists of the scientific group also conducted a study of financial monitoring.
In this experiment, three groups stood against a person under different circumstances.
The control group was simply informed of the real value of the product in question, and its members were warned.
In addition, he was promised that if they won, they would receive $15 more.
On the contrary, the third group received $15 just before the summit, but in case the group members lost the summit, even the money was lost.
So the only difference between the two groups was that for one, the triumph was highlighted and for the other failure.
However, testing the hypotheses of neurologists, members of the group who played "against failure" were willing to place more than members of the control group and the "winner" group.
"These results cannot be deduced from any previous economic theory.
So far, they have explained the phenomena of the substations only with the joy of winning and with the prevention of risks.
Only visual neurological methods helped to resolve this contradiction between the two theories, so that we now come to a third explanation" - Andrew Schotter, professor of the University of New York economy.
Hepatitis: When should you go to the doctor?
In the world about 50 million people suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, and chronic liver disease in Hungary is considered one of the main causes of death.
The number of infected people in this country is estimated at one hundred thousand, but only seven thousand receive treatment because many of the patients do not know that they are infected.
The name of hepatitis is the common name of different liver diseases caused by viruses.
The symptoms are very similar; they are characteristic of the infection of the liver and the ecteric, but their pathogens and occasional diseases are very different.
Hepatitis virus depending on the pathogen agent is spread through two main forms: hepatitis A and E via food (e.g. with water or contaminated food), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and body humor (esperma, vaginal humor, saliva).
Travellers are recommended to be protected by vaccine against virus A and B, against C no vaccines.
The symptoms of hepatitis A occur two or three weeks after consumption of the infected food, manifested by a poor general state, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After this appears in the skin and in the white of the eyes icterity, the excretion becomes clear, the dark color origin and the healing can last even two to three weeks.
Each year, one million people die in cancer and liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B, the most serious forms of this disease.
The main reason for this is that according to calculations, only 1 in 10 infected people receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C may also have very serious consequences: hepatic cirrhosis and even cancer may occur without treatment.
Most of the infected people do not know that they are sick because this pathological agent in the form of paulatin destroys the liver cells and often the first symptoms appear only 20-30 years later.
It is therefore very important for early recognition, systematic medical control.
This disease is much more common in three groups: people who had blood transfusions before 1991, drug users and tattoos.
Currently there are about 200 million people in the world who suffer from chronic hepatitis C.
Since this disease can also be discovered with routine laboratory control, it is worth consulting the family doctor when experiencing some unknown symptoms.
The disease has treatment if it is discovered in time, it is possible to eliminate the organism's virus, thereby eliminating the infection and preventing cancer.
30 September is the World Hepatitis Day, which was organized for the first time in 2004 by organizations representing the sick.
Its aim is to address the causes of chronic liver infections caused by viruses and the importance of their early recognition.
