According to a recent study, religious faith has a calming effect that also eased the death of Catholic martyrs.
The scientists at Oxford University conducted an interesting experiment: they analyzed how religious belief influences human suffering - reported the British Telegraph.
Within the framework of this unique experiment, they applied electric shock to 12 Catholic believers and the same number of atheists, while they were all looking at a painting of the Virgin Mary.
As a result, Catholic believers were able to exclude most of their pain.
Thanks to the human brain scan technique, it was possible to verify that Catholic believers were able to activate that part of their brain that is responsible for the regulation of pain.
